Author: ClassicMarketing2
Text: I find that many can be really oblivious to binging and that it's one of the last things to cross their mind. Even if they saw the food they might just have thought you were really hungry, hadn't eaten much earlier, etc that's if they even noticed. Before becoming bulimic I'd never have thought someone was binging if they ate a lot. We're just more focused on seeing 'signs' like that. Hope this helps x

Author: Little_Bear716
Text: Like I’m just staring at my food right now and idk if I eat it or just toss it or what I’m supposed to do now that I’ve been caught.   The poor person in me says eat it because I spent money on it but the ED part says don’t fucking touch it. You can’t be embarrassed if you don’t actually eat it.
